# Skill: Testing

{% if stack == "python" %}## Framework

pytest — `uv run pytest -q`

{% elif stack == "node" %}## Framework

jest / vitest — `npm test`

{% elif stack == "go" %}## Framework

go test — `go test ./...`

{% endif %}## Rules

REQUIRE:
- Tests for all public functions and behavior changes
{% if stack == "python" %}- Descriptive test names: `test_<subject>_<condition>_<expected_outcome>`
- Use `tmp_path` fixture for filesystem-touching tests
{% elif stack == "go" %}- Table-driven tests for multiple input variations
{% endif %}- Isolated tests: no shared mutable state between tests

REJECT if:
- Tests call external services without mocking
- Empty test body
- Tests depend on execution order

PREFER:
{% if stack == "python" %}- `pytest.mark.parametrize` over repeated similar test functions
- Factory fixtures over inline setup in each test
- `conftest.py` for shared fixtures within a package
{% elif stack == "node" %}- `describe` / `it` structure for grouping related tests
- `beforeEach` / `afterEach` for setup and teardown
{% elif stack == "go" %}- Subtests (`t.Run`) for grouping related cases
- Testify for assertions
{% else %}- Parameterized tests over repeated similar test functions
{% endif %}
